			Alpaca-ranching has been an extremely successful lifestyle change for us.  A ranch tour is by far the best way to experience whether it might also work for you.  Alpacas at Lone Ranch offers a free personalized tour of alpaca-ranching. <br>
			<br>

			The ranch is conveniently located between Eagle Point and Shady Cove, 4.5 miles west on Oregon’s Scenic Byway 234 in the beautiful Upper Rogue Valley close to historic Jacksonville, the cultural treasure of Ashland, and the unsurpassed beauty of Crater Lake.<br>
			<br>
			<ul>
				<li>Your entire family can get a first-hand, up-close look at both the Animal and Business sides of operations. </li>
				<li>A casual walk through <a href = "TypicalDay.asp" class = "body">typical and special days</a> of alpaca-ranching can give many answers and also help to stimulate the right questions. </li>
				<li>It may seem early to think about <a href = "TypicalInvestment.asp" class = "body">Pricing Alpacas</a>, but it is an important component of evaluating whether alpaca-ranching will be right for you.  The price of a starter package is usually far below the value of the individual animals.  Pick out your favorites and get an actual quote of examples. </li>
				<li>Families may choose to combine this tour with a memorable vacation/visit to Jacksonville, Ashland and Crater Lake.</li>
			</ul>
